modules.description: This module provided legacy type definitions and signatures for MirageOS components such as network, block, and key/value store devices, primarily used for composing unikernels with Lwt-based asynchronous operations. It worked with abstract types representing devices like consoles, block storage, and network endpoints, enabling their use in a type-safe, modular fashion. Concrete use cases included building custom unikernels with statically configured storage backends or network interfaces.
